        "content": "<p>If I have <code>s : Finset α</code> and <code>f : (x : α) → x ∈ s → β</code>, is there any easy way I can take the image of <code>s</code> under <code>f</code>?</p>",
        "id": 466565228,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1725118199
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Obviously I can first define some auxiliary <code>f' : α → β</code> that takes garbage when <code>x ∉ s</code>, but I'd like to avoid extra work if possible.</p>",
        "id": 466565446,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1725118237
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe I can first convert <code>s : Finset α</code> into <code>s' : Finset {x : α // x ∈ s}</code> and just use <code>image</code> on that? No idea if that's possible or reasonable</p>",
        "id": 466566402,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1725118430
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, I can use <code>Finset.subtype</code> for that</p>",
        "id": 466566647,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1725118486
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>is there a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Finset.attach#doc\">docs#Finset.attach</a> or <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Finset.pmap#doc\">docs#Finset.pmap</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 466567238,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1725118707
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yes to the first, so you can use it to construct your set as an image</p>",
